1. *Vozača* sam video kako vozi kroz grad. (*I saw the driver driving through the city.*)
2. Nisam siguran da li je *vozača* bilo u automobilu. (*I'm not sure if there was a driver in the car.*)
3. *Vozača* je uhvatio policajac jer je vozio prebrzo. (*The policeman caught the driver for speeding.*)
4. Molim vas, pitajte *vozača* da li ide do centra grada. (*Please ask the driver if he goes to the city center.*)
5. Kada se sudarila dva automobila, *vozač* jednog od njih je preminuo. (*When two cars collided, the driver of one of them died.*)
6. *Vozači* kamiona moraju da se pridržavaju ograničenja brzine na auto-putu. (*Truck drivers must adhere to speed limits on the highway.*)
7. Policija traži informacije o *vozačima* koji su pobegli sa lica mesta nakon saobraćajne nesreće. (*Police are seeking information about the drivers who fled the scene after the accident.*)
8. Ova firma ima mnogo iskusnih *vozača* koji voze kamione širom zemlje. (*This company has many experienced drivers who drive trucks throughout the country.*)
9. *Vozaču* je bilo otežano vidno polje zbog snega koji je padao. (*The driver had reduced visibility due to the snowfall.*)
10. Nakon dugog putovanja, *vozači* su se odmarali u hotelu pre nego što nastave dalje. (*After a long journey, the drivers rested at the hotel before continuing.*)

Note: In Serbian language, the word "vozača" can have different forms and endings depending on its grammatical role in a sentence (nominative, genitive, dative, accusative, etc.) and number (singular or plural). In the sentences above, the word "vozača" appears in different forms and positions to illustrate some of these possibilities.